data.name: Find the divisors! (Performance)
data.description:
This kata is based off another popular kata of the same name, but with much stricter performance requirements and one or two additions.

The goal is to find all the divisors of a given number (except 1 and itself), and return them as an array (the order doesn't matter). If the number is prime, return "(number) is prime". If the number is anything other than an integer, or < 2, throw an error of your choosing (we wouldn't want our function returning something like 'string is prime')

Examples:
```javascript
getDivs(625) => [5, 25, 125]
getDivs(2136195961) => [46219]
getDivs("-22.5") => Should throw an error
getDivs(872568404527691) => '872568404527691 is prime'
```
Note that although the performance requirements are astronomically higher than "Find the divisors!", you still don't need the world's fastest algorithm, or one that uses pure math.

Make sure you're not doing more work than you need to.

Have fun!
